// This gitignore pattern ignores all files and directories within the ./logs folder.
// The /* wildcard matches any file or directory name at that level.
// Note: This will ignore contents of logs/, but the logs/ directory itself
// may still be tracked if it was previously committed. Consider using logs/
// (without the /*) to ignore the entire directory, or add logs/ to .gitignore
// if you want to ensure the directory itself is also ignored.
./logs/*

